# API Integration Rules

Use a service layer for backend communication.

Environment variables:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL should point to the NestJS backend.

Service rules:
- Keep fetch wrapper in src/lib/apiClient.js.
- Keep feature-specific API calls in src/services.
- Do not call fetch directly from many UI components.
- Return normalized frontend-friendly data.
- While backend is unavailable, services may fall back to mock data.

Expected future backend endpoints:
- GET /predictions/today
- GET /predictions/matches/:matchId
- POST /predictions/matches/:matchId/unlock-free
- GET /predictions/history
- GET /bankroll
- GET /bankroll/performance

Security:
- Do not store JWT tokens in code.
- Do not expose OpenAI keys in frontend.
- Do not expose raw AI prompts in public pages.
- Never rely on frontend blur as real security.
